definitions.definition: A module making up part of a larger module.
examples: The first-year English Literature module consists of three submodules .

definitions.definition: A module contained in a larger module , both over the same ring , such that the ring multiplication in the former is a restriction of that in the latter.

main_definition: A module making up part of a larger module.
secondary_definitions: ( algebra ) A module contained in a larger module , both over the same ring , such that the ring multiplication in the former is a restriction of that in the latter.
